India gets its own GPS with successful launch of 7th navigation satellite
India on Thursday entered an exclusive club of five nations that have their own satellite navigation and positioning system with the launch of IRNSS-1G,known as Navic, the countryâ€™s seventh navigation satellite. With this, the country will not have to depend on a foreign power for military navigation.
